<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 16 at 2:26PM CDT  by NWS Mobile</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of central Choctaw and
northwestern Clarke Counties through 315 PM CDT...
At 225 PM CDT, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated
strong thunderstorms along a line extending from near Myrtlewood to 5
miles northwest of Toxey. Movement was east at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Butler, Pennington, Gilbertown and Toxey.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
